# Working Style

- Make minimal, targeted changes that satisfy the request.
- Explain changes in detail and include rationale.
- Prefer editing existing code over large refactors.
- Keep modifications localized; avoid unrelated cleanup.

# Safety and Clarity

- If a change affects behavior, call it out explicitly.
- Highlight any assumptions made while implementing.
- Suggest tests to run when relevant.
